# Calculating length of stay from difference (subtraction) between Discharge Time and Admission Time 
#(Length of Stay = Discharge Time - Admission Time)

def diff(a, b):
    return b - a

df['length_of_stay'] = df.apply(
    lambda x: diff(x['admittime'], x['dischtime']), axis=1)

# Converting date of birth (dob) to date
df['dob'] = pd.to_datetime(df['dob']).dt.date

# Converting admission date (admittime) to date
df['admittime'] = pd.to_datetime(df['admittime']).dt.date

# Calculating patient age (age = admission time - date of birth)
df['age'] = df.apply(lambda e: (e['admittime'] - e['dob']).days/365, axis=1)

# Returning 89 to all values greater than 89 in the age column
df['age'] = df['age'].apply(lambda x: 89 if x > 89 else x).astype('int')

## Change values entries starting with alphabet letters (a-zA-Z) to numbers (3 digits)

# Creating a new column for ICD9 Code
df_diagnoses['new_icd9_code'] = df_diagnoses['icd9_code']

# Selecting only numeric values for ICD9 Code
df_diagnoses = df_diagnoses[~df_diagnoses['new_icd9_code'].str.contains("[a-zA-Z]").fillna(False)]

# Filling the missing values (entries starting with alphabet letters (a-zA-Z)) with 999
df_diagnoses['new_icd9_code'].fillna(value='999', inplace=True)

# Reducing the icd9 codes to the first three digits
df_diagnoses['new_icd9_code'] = df_diagnoses['new_icd9_code'].str.slice(start=0, stop=3, step=1)
df_diagnoses['new_icd9_code'] = df_diagnoses['new_icd9_code'].astype(int)

# Converting the ICD9_Codes into Categorical diseases using a list of codes 
# for International Statistical Classification of Diseases and Related Health Problems

#ICD-9 codes 001139: infectious and parasitic diseases
#ICD-9 codes 140239: neoplasms
#ICD-9 codes 240279: endocrine, nutritional and metabolic diseases, and immunity disorders
#ICD-9 codes 280289: diseases of the blood and blood-forming organs
#ICD-9 codes 290319: mental disorders
#ICD-9 codes 320389: diseases of the nervous system and sense organs
#ICD-9 codes 390459: diseases of the circulatory system
#ICD-9 codes 460519: diseases of the respiratory system
#ICD-9 codes 520579: diseases of the digestive system
#ICD-9 codes 580629: diseases of the genitourinary system
#ICD-9 codes 630679: complications of pregnancy, childbirth, and the puerperium
#ICD-9 codes 680709: diseases of the skin and subcutaneous tissue
#ICD-9 codes 710739: diseases of the musculoskeletal system and connective tissue
#ICD-9 codes 740759: congenital anomalies
#ICD-9 codes 760779: certain conditions originating in the perinatal period
#ICD-9 codes 780799: symptoms, signs, and ill-defined conditions
#ICD-9 codes 800999: injury and poisoning
#ICD-9 codes E and V codes: external causes of injury and supplemental classification
#Source: Wikipedia

# Defining code range to match with ICD9 Code diseases classification
bins = [1,139,239,279,289,319,389,459,519,579,629,679,709,739,759,779,799,999] 

# Defining the labels for returned bins
diseases_classification = ["Infectious","Neoplasms","Endocrine","Blood","Mental Disorders","Nervous System","Circulatory System",
                   "Respiratory System","Digestive System","Genitourinary System","Pregnancy","Skin","Musculoskeletal System",
                   "Congenital Anomalies","Perinatal Period","Ill-Defined Conditions","Injury and Poisoning"] 

# Creating disease classification from matching bins with labels
df_diagnoses['diseases_classification'] = pd.cut(df_diagnoses['new_icd9_code'],bins,labels = diseases_classification)

from scipy.stats import kruskal

# Carrying out krustal test on the categorical data

# Adimission type 
admission_cats = df.groupby('admission_type')['length_of_stay'].apply(list)
H_admissin, p_admission = kruskal(*admission_cats)


# Discharge Location
discharge_cats = df.groupby('discharge_location')['length_of_stay'].apply(list)
H_discharge, p_discharge = kruskal(*discharge_cats)


#Insurance
insurance_cats = df.groupby('insurance')['length_of_stay'].apply(list)
H_insurance, p_insurance = kruskal(*insurance_cats)


#religion 

religion_cats = df.groupby('religion')['length_of_stay'].apply(list)
H_religion, p_religion = kruskal(*religion_cats)


#Marital_status 
                 
marital_cats = df.groupby('marital_status')['length_of_stay'].apply(list)
H_marital, p_marital = kruskal(*marital_cats)
   
                 
#Ethnicity

ethnicity_cats = df.groupby('ethnicity')['length_of_stay'].apply(list)
H_ethnicity, p_ethnicity = kruskal(*ethnicity_cats)


#Gender  
                 
gender_cats = df.groupby('gender')['length_of_stay'].apply(list)
H_gender, p_gender = kruskal(*gender_cats)
                 
#Age

Hyperparameter tuning (RandomizedSearchCV)¶
In [97]:
# Hyperparameter distribution
parameter_distribution = {
    "max_depth": randint(1, 8),
    "n_estimators": randint(100, 400),
    "min_samples_leaf": randint(1, 10),
    "max_features": ["auto", "sqrt", "log2", None],
    "random_state": [42]
}

# Defining Random forest
rf = RandomForestRegressor()

# Create Randomized Search
random_search = RandomizedSearchCV(estimator=rf, param_distributions=parameter_distribution, cv=5, n_iter=20, n_jobs=-1)

# Fit the randomized search to the data
random_search.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Print the best hyperparameters and MSE
print(f"Best hyperparameters: {random_search.best_params_}")
print(f"Mean squared error: {random_search.best_score_}")
